%N A265271 Least positive real z such that 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z} / 2^n, where {x} denotes the fractional part of x.
%C A265271 This constant is transcendental.
%C A265271 The rational approximation z ~ 345131297/1073741820 is accurate to over 5 million digits.
%C A265271 This constant is one of 6 solutions to the equation 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z}/2^n, where z is in the interval (0,1) - see cross-references for other solutions.
%C A265271 The complement to this constant is given by A265276.
%H A265271 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/DevilsStaircase.html">Devil's Staircase</a>.
%H A265271 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>
%F A265271 The constant z satisfies:
%F A265271 (1) 2*z - 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} [n*z] / 2^n,
%F A265271 (2) 2*z - 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/z],
%F A265271 (3) 3/2 - 2*z = Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/(1-z)],
%F A265271 (4) 3/2 - 2*z = Sum_{n>=1} [n*(1-z)] / 2^n,
%F A265271 (5) 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*(1-z)} / 2^n,
%F A265271 where [x] denotes the integer floor function of x.
%e A265271 z = 0.321428569299834107234456044563859867169931036121886358119124...
%e A265271 where z satisfies
%e A265271 (0) 1/2 = {z}/2 + {2*z}/2^2 + {3*z}/2^3 + {4*z}/2^4 + {5*z}/2^5 +...
